{code:sql}
set spark.sql.session.timeZone = America/Los_Angeles;
select to_timestamp(timestamp_ntz'2000-09-01 01:00:00', '')
{code}

This returns `2000-08-31`, when it should return `2000-09-01`.

This is because `ParseToDate` and `ParseToTimestamp` do not handle `TimestampNTZ` when creating `GetTimestamp`, which runs into issues when `GetTimestamp` is evaluated and then casted to date.

